# AWS credentials for the legacy docker-compose harness.
#
# PURGED 2026-07-24 (employee-documents Phase 1, spec §8 "also fixed in
# passing"): this file carried long-lived static IAM keys committed to
# git. The committed key (AKIA5SCDPPSOHCY7OKPF) was verified to no
# longer exist in IAM — the leaked value is inert — and the plaintext
# was removed from the working tree. Old git history still shows the
# dead key pair; that is acceptable only because the key is deleted.
#
# If a local compose run genuinely needs AWS access, export short-lived
# credentials into your shell before `docker compose up` — NEVER commit
# values to this file. docker-compose env_file does not interpolate, so
# pass real values via the environment/overrides instead.
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
